reviews: Bought three touques, and two of them seem real. Black one is made in Canada, blue one in the USA. The Coal Heather is made in China. It also doesn‚Äôt have a genuine label inside. On Carhartt.com it says all touques with exception of Brite orange, Brite Lime, Black, and Dark Green is made in USA. The black one is made in Canada, and is of very good quality, but the Coal Heather is supposed to be made in USA, but the tag doesn‚Äôt say that. It is also of poor quality. It. Has loose stitching, its too tight, the fabric is rough, too small, and the outside label is noticeably shinier than the other two. The other two are not the same as each other either, but they seem higher quality though.
Keeps my head warm, doesn't stretch out after wearing all day and best of all, no itchy toque head. Price and free shipping, can' t beat it!!

I read a lot of reviews on both the adult and toddler toques/"hats" and was concerned about quality, size, and colour accuracy. I wanted to get matching toques for my 1 year old son and myself. I bit the bullet because they were such a great price. They came super fast and I was very pleased when I opened the package. While the Amazon picture for the Carhartt brown hat was darker than the one for the adult hat, when they arrived, both were the legitimate Carhartt Brown colour. Matchy matchy! (note, the picture I provided has poor lighting, so they look a bit different, but trust me, they could have come from the exact same batch of dye). I was also worried that the toddler hat would stand very tall and loose (as shown in the Amazon advertisement photo), but no, it is about the same proportion as the adult toque.
Both are of the exact same quality and fabric. Both have legit Made in USA tags on them. My only issue is that my 1 year old has a big head and I might need to exchange this toque for the young child size.

Pro's
+ Very warm (almost hot)
+ Highly adjustable fold (double cover for the ears)
+ Label can be removed easily with an exacto knife
+ Seems to be fairly durable and well made

- Each hat color seems have a slightly different size/elasticity (could be caused by washing and/or due to use)
- Label sits very high on your head if you wear this toque as you would a "normal" toque (can easily be removed)
This is my favourite hat of all time. I wear it nearly every day and it fits great. I get compliments on it all the time and it‚Äôs great value for the quality of the hat.

review_title: Elegant Hat (or Touque as they call it here in Canada)
reviews:
Ordered the Dark Brown/Sandstone color & it looks great! It's made in USA & the one-size-fits-all holds definitely true. It easily fits a naughty 5 year old or even naughtier 30+ year old.

The 100% Acrylic thing will be confirmed within a year or two. I got a Genuine Levis Touque from a Levis store last time & within a year, it has lint hanging all over it so I have trust issue now until I see something last.

I bought three different colours. There was a slight difference in fit between the three. I have a very large head were my wife has normal size. Her fit is fine, mine is a teeny bit smug. Pull the turned up flap down and there is a very relaxed fit. When I pull the brim up as shown in pics mine is snug. But as I said, I have a large Mellon. Overall the are perfectly fine and a decent product. No buyers remorse. The cobalt blue or whatever it's called is a bright vibrant blue.

I have a few Carhartt hats that I've bought in store and this one here fits in with them as per the same good quality material and great look. I've noticed that quite a few reviews say that this hat had a loose fit on them but for me that was not the case at all. I'm not sure if they actually sent me a children's hat, but for some reason it just seems really small on my head whereas the other ones I have have a much looser fit (both tighter around the base and shorter at the top point). It could be because my older ones are stretched a bit from use, but I do not recall them ever feeling "tight" even when I first purchased them. Still a great hat though so I'll be keeping it for sure - maybe just try to stretch it out first lol

I had this beanie for about 2 weeks, and after 3 washes it is all stretched out. Not just a little. Its has lost all its elasticity. I've never had a touque do this. Maybe I got a fake one, or washed it wrong. Not what I expect from Carhartt. Just sucks because it is completely useless. 2 weeks and I'm throwing it out. It was annoying enough to leave this review. Hopefully others have better luck.

After reading a couple other reviews, it looks like it's kind of a gamble as to what you get. Mine is Chinese made. Apparently other people are getting products made domestically. Lucky me üòÅ

review_title: It‚Äôs actually a really good hat!
reviews: It‚Äôs a genuine Carhartt hat. It came with tags and everything, the material is so nice, it keeps my head warm and they‚Äôre trendy. The colours are spot on. I don‚Äôt have anything bad to say about them. I also got the brown one, it looks exactly like the orange- it‚Äôs not letting me put a photo so ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

I love wearing hats and thought this style was cute for the wintertime - but man does this thing fit small. I don't consider myself to have a large head but I find this hat trying to squeeze the life out of my noggin, I end up with little indents on my forehead from the elastic - like an inverted Thanos chin on my face. Not to mention, it's so tight that it can essentially hold my sunglasses in place without them even touching my face. Did I get a lemon, or has my head grown? Maybe it's just this colour? I don't know.

review_title: Great hat for the price, but a little too small for me
reviews: The hat is great quality, but it seems to be too small for me, not to the point of returning it, but to the point of me having to leave it stretched over the back of a chair whenever I'm not wearing it. They're pretty inexpensive, so I'm only taking away one star. Also, while trying to stretch it, the Carhartt patch ripped off the front, but it didn't leave any damage behind to the hat, so I'm not taking a star off. Well made hat for the price - if it was a little bigger I'd order a few more.

review_title: Great for people with large heads! Keeps you warm and good quality!
reviews: I actually purchased this toque because I have a larger head and noticed someone in the reviews stated it ran a bit bigger. Fits really well! I live in Canada and I wore this toque all winter, all the way down to -25 degrees C. Keeps you super warm and is really comfortable. Only issue I had, and for around $10 I cannot really complain about it, at the end of the Winter the hat did stretch out a bit.

Ordered 2 men's Carthatt acrylic hats the exact same style and both were one size fits all. Bought them for a Christmas stocking gift. One fit fine but the red one was too tight and was not as flexible as the black one. A few family members tried it on and they all found it fit too small. It may fit a boy's small head but not an average man's size head. I can't return it because I bought it too early for Christmas so I am stuck with it. Note that it was only the red one that was too small.

review_title: Red/navy is slightly darker than expected but still awesome
reviews: Yep it's a soft, well fitting, authentic Carhartt beanie. I tried to get an accurate photo of the color of this thing but my pic came out a bit lighter than what I see in person; the thing about this type of color is that it changes depending on the lighting. Regardless I think it's awesome if you want a speckled red hat

It‚Äôs a little more purple than the photo but I actually like it more! Comfy, warm and nice quality!

Good toque for Canadian winters!

Went to my parents house wearing a hat and my step-dad saw it and commented that he was going to take it so i bought an extra one for christmas for him. great quality bought one for my boyfriend who works outside as well. he says it keeps his head nice and warm. as pictured.

I actually love this beanie, it‚Äôs unisex so anyone can wear it! The colour/casual look goes well with every single fall/winter outfit. It‚Äôs also super warm, which is really nice if you live in a colder climate.

The only downside is the length of the beanie, there‚Äôs excess fabric that sticks out from the top. However, some people love that, it‚Äôs a look on its own. (Very structured beanie)

The colour is very nice (wine) and true to the photo, but the hat fits extremely smaller than anticipated. As a woman with a fairly small to average sized head, I'm not sure how this would fit a man's head comfortably. It certainly doesn't have that Carhatt "look" that has become so popular. Maybe it will stretch over time, but not super thrilled with it.

I bought this for my son last autumn to go with his new jacket and after several washes and hanging to dry it is still going strong. Thanks Carhardt for continuing to make a durable product that works as hard as the people that wear it.

Worth every penny

It‚Äôs really warm though, and I‚Äôm sure I‚Äôll be plenty warm even in the cold winter months where I live in the Northern part of our province.

review_title: It so cold now in Quebec, that hell itself is frozen.
reviews:
Greetings,

The saying that synthetic matter will keep you as warm and will be more agreeable to wear is completely false.When it is cold, nothing beats wool,
and at -30 C, there is one and only one thing; the Russian Chapka, a fur hat that you wear with the flaps up attached over the head in mild colds, with flaps down, covering your ears in the coldest of situations. A warmer temperature will give me plenty of occasions to wear my blue Carhartt.

Regards and Happy New Year,

review_title: Low Quality Work, 3 hats all same defect
reviews: I have now had 3 different hats, all dark blue navy, start to come apart at the top of the hat within 2 weeks of regular use. First one i returned a got an exchange, the second one was worse and started coming apart one day into use. This third one i figured i would give one last try and its come apart after 1 weekend of ice fishing. A friend has a brown which is fine and still holding up, so mabye its just this version (it says "made in USA of US and imported parts.....) which are made trash. The hats are warm and look nice, but the quality of carhartt gear has steadily gone down now that all the casual normies start wearing construction gear to identify with the working class. Make no mistake, just like every other company that gets picked up by the mainstream, this company has its days numbered

review_title: Fake carhartt for some colors and the real ones are HUGE
reviews: FAKE!! You can clearly see the difference in the size and logo between the blue (fake) and black(real) The writing isnt the same font at all and carhartt C is too yellow and non textured. Also didnt come with tags. Also the black hat that was ordered for me as a gift is HUGE measuring 11 inches long with the flap folded up.. so I dont know how this size would fit all. Honestly the fake one fits better.

For some reason the label looks to be a cheap rendition of Carthart, quality of the hat is good but the logo looks a bit like a knock off and has some bleeding in it from the ink. cant attach photo as sent as gift already
